Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the decidability and expressiveness of mu-calculus on data words and data omega-words, which are logical structures. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the automata characterizations of the logic fragments. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with data words and data omega-words, which are data structures. 
- cs.LT (Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses the compositions of formulas and their automata characterizations, which are related to learning. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with the expressiveness of mu-calculus, which is a formal language used in programming language theory.
